    Description: The Apache Sling API defines an extension to the Servlet        API 2.4 to provide access to content and unified access        to request parameters hiding the differences between the        different methods of transferring parameters from client        to server.     console.categories=[core, nodes]
    errorpages.path=meta/errorpages
    node.default.filter=and{Name(-'^rep:(repo)?[Pp]olicy$'),Path(-'^/bin(/.*)?$,^/services(/.*)?$,^/servlet(/.*)?$,^/(jcr:)?system(/.*)?$')}
    node.orderable.filter=or{Type(node:orderable),PrimaryType(+'^.*([Oo]rdered|[Pp]age).*$,^sling:(Mapping)$,^nt:(unstructured|frozenNode)$,^rep:(ACL|Members|system)$')}
    node.page.filter=or{ResourceType(+'^[a-z]+:.*([Ss]ite|[Pp]age)$'),and{PrimaryType(+'^nt:file$'),MimeType(+'^text/html$')}}
    node.referenceable.filter=Type(mix:referenceable)
    node.servlet.enabled=true
    node.source.filter=PrimaryType(-'^cpp:(Statistics)$,^rep:(.+)$')
    package.servlet.enabled=true
    property.servlet.enabled=true
    query.result.limit=500
    query.templates=[/content/test ${text}, ${path}//${name}[jcr:contains(.,'${word}')]]
    security.servlet.enabled=true
    service.pid=com.composum.sling.nodes.NodesConfigImpl
    service.vendor=IST GmbH Dresden
    source.servlet.enabled=true
    tree.intermediate.filter=or{Folder(),PrimaryType(+'^dam:Asset(Content)?$')}
    usermanagement.servlet.enabled=true
    version.servlet.enabled=true
